title: After Tough Tests, Expectations High for UMD
text:
After Tough Tests, Expectations High for UMD 
By Zach Schneider October 13, 2015 Updated Oct 13, 2015 at 10:49 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) football team has come through the toughest part of its 2015 schedule with a (4-2) overall record, but head coach Curt Wiese warns against his team easing off the gas headed to the final five contests. 
UMD's first six opponents are a combined (25-11) in 2015, and the next five opponents are a combined (6-24). 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Still, Wiese says his team has plenty to focus on moving forward. 
"This is about us getting better technically as a football team," he said. "Going back to the St. Cloud State and Upper Iowa games, there are things we can improve. We haven't played a perfect football game, and that's what we'll strive for this week." 
UMD is on the road this Saturday to (0-6) Mary, with kickoff scheduled for 2:30 p.m.
